    profit — including companies, partnerships, sole proprietorships with
    employees or contractors, non-profits, charities, government or public
    bodies, educational institutions, clubs, associations, and collectives.
    Any commercial use by a single individual is also treated as use by an
    Organization for the purposes of this license.

1.3 "Configuration" means using the Software through its documented,
    officially provided settings, command-line flags, environment variables,
    configuration files, profiles, and documented extension points, without
    altering the Software's source code, compiled artifacts, behavior beyond
    what those options expose, visual appearance, or Branding.

1.4 "Modification" (or to "Customize") means anything beyond Configuration,
    including but not limited to: altering, adapting, or translating the source
    code or compiled artifacts; creating derivative works; changing the
    Software's behavior, features, or workflows other than through
    Configuration; changing its visual appearance, including colors, themes,
    layout, typography, or user-interface text; and adding, altering, removing,
    obscuring, or replacing Branding.

1.5 "Branding" means the names, logos, marks, product identifiers, copyright
    notices, and attribution identifying the Software or the Licensor —
    including the name "lo-agent" and the Licensor's name — wherever they
    appear in the Software, its interfaces, its output, or its documentation.

1.6 "Enterprise License" means a separate written agreement between the
    Licensor and an Organization granting rights beyond those in this license.

